The paper discusses a new generation of dynamic network architectures that incorporate cognitive capabilities to exploit underutilized spectrum in a more flexible and intelligent way. This aligns with the research areas of network infrastructure, information theory, security and privacy, systems and control, and multimedia. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Other likely sub-categories include cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
